-- Serbia Water Utility in Novi Sad Plans Water Works, SeeNews Says
-- B y   R a n d a l l   H a c k l e y
-- 2013-01-09T17:58:07Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-01-09/serbia-water-utility-in-novi-sad-plans-water-works-seenews-says.html
The water utility serving the Serbian
city of Novi Sad plans to invest at least 2.5 billion dinars
($29.2 million) in water and sewer system upgrades this year,
SeeNews reported, citing a statement from the company.  Vodovod i Kanalizacija plans to outfit a water plant on the
Danube River with an ozonation and activated carbon filtration
system and add a reservoir to stabilize water supplies, the
report said, citing the utility. Novi Sad is the capital of
